issue.title: Added partial support for stm32f103 bluepill board
issue.body:
This is based on similar board stm32vl_discovery.
Embox boots successfully and even prints out some info, but you can't input anything to console,
probably because clocks weren't adjusted for this MCU.

comment.body: It's better to use `@BuildArtefactPath` for `platform.stm32.f1.stm32f103_bluepill.stm32f103_bluepill_conf` module for this purpose

issue.title: sshd (dropbear) rejects second connection
issue.body:
There is an sshd server in Embox - third-party/dropbear/ (what dropbear is - https://matt.ucc.asn.au/dropbear/dropbear.html). So it is a third party application ported to Embox.

_How to start dropbear?_
* `make confload-x86/qemu`. Then add `include third_party.dropbear.dropbear` in conf/mods.config, also add `"service dropbear -F"` in conf/system_start.inc. Build embox.
* Start Embox
* Connect to sshd from your Linux host:
```
$ ssh root@10.0.2.16
root@10.0.2.16's password: 
[5] Jan 01 00:00:58 wtmp_write: problem writing /var/log/wtmp: No such entity
root@embox:/#exit
Connection to 10.0.2.16 closed.
```
_What's the problem?_
Try to connect once more:
```
$ ssh root@10.0.2.16
ssh: connect to host 10.0.2.16 port 22: Connection refused
```

This issue is probably not so easy, but we do not expect fast bug fix from you, but the problem investigation with `gdb`.

release.name: v0.6.0
release.body:
* Improved ARM arch
* Improved RISC-V arch
* Cleaned AARCH64 arch
* Improved dev-tree for STM32
* Improved SPI, I2C, UART subsystems
* Improved GDB server
* Improved file subsystem
* Improved block & char devices subsystem
* Improved network subsystem
* Ported to nucleo f207zg
* Ported to RC-Module mb77.07
* Added message buffer from sys/ipc.h
* Updated dropbear and some other third-party projects
* A lot of improvements and fixes
